interfaces.Calendar

  • Packages that use Calendar 
    Package Description
    implementations  

    • Uses of Calendar in implementations

      Classes in implementations that implement Calendar 
      Modifier and Type Class and Description
      class  CalendarImpl
      This class implements a Calendar using a SharkKB to store and receive Appointments from and a SyncKP to transfer Appointments and Comments to other instances.
      Constructors in implementations with parameters of type Calendar 
      Constructor and Description
      AppointmentCPListener(Calendar cal, net.sharkfw.knowledgeBase.SharkKB kb, ChangedAppointmentListener handler)
      This constructor initializes this AppointmentCPListener so that the passed ChangedAppointmentListener can handle a new Appointment or Comment.
      AppointmentImpl(Calendar cal, net.sharkfw.knowledgeBase.SharkKB kb, net.sharkfw.knowledgeBase.ContextPoint cp, net.sharkfw.knowledgeBase.Information i)
      This constructor creates an Appointment that represents an Information in a SharkKB that was created by CalendarImpl.
      AppointmentUpdatedListener(Calendar cal, ChangedAppointmentListener update_handler, net.sharkfw.knowledgeBase.SharkKB kb)
      This constructor takes care that the passed ChangedAppointmentListener can be called on new Appointments and Comments
      CommentImpl(Calendar cal, Appointment app, net.sharkfw.knowledgeBase.Information i)
      Constructor creates a representation of a Comment stored in the passed Information and managed by the passed Calendar.
